edia:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/ce6496e0-51a0-11ee-badb-e7408aa44fba" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Apple]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Apple's iPhone 15 Pro and 15 Pro Max]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[iPhone 15 Pro and 15 Pro Max ]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[iPhone 15 Pro Max first impressions: Lights, camera, action button]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/everything-announced-at-todays-apple-event-iphone-15-usb-c-apple-watch-series-9-and-more-200111613.html">在今天的 iPhone 15 发布会</a>上，苹果公司花了很多时间（和金钱）谈论其“苹果 2030”碳中和和环境责任愿景。讽刺的是，苹果希望你购买更多 iPhone，为此，它推出了功能略有不同的新型号，这样你就会花钱。随着今年<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apples-iphone-15-has-a-48-megapixel-camera-and-the-dynamic-island-174520662.html">iPhone 15</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-has-a-titanium-case-an-action-button-and-usb-c-181257580.html">iPhone 15 Pro 的</a>推出，苹果也开始遵守<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/eu-usb-c-wired-charging-deadline-152454857.html">欧盟法规</a>，该法规要求明年底前生产的所有新设备都支持 USB-C 充电。虽然这对大多数人来说是个好消息，但这确实意味着那些可能还没有兼容电线的人将不得不再次购买新的充电器。</p><p>除了新端口（再见，闪电！）之外，iPhone 15 Pro Max 还配备了四棱镜系统的变焦镜头，以及取代侧面滑动开关的所谓操作按钮。在基本款 iPhone 15 和 15 Plus 上，我们也告别了刘海，向<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-iphone-14-pro-dynamic-island-181347737.html">动态岛</a>问好。看起来 iPhone 15 系列让我们留下了很多过去的东西，希望能有更好的东西。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="01874a08dfbb4780adf22bd1c42d1f17"><div style="left:0;width:100%;height:0;position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/zLctc3-QcrM?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div></div><p>这些变化中最有趣的是“操作”按钮，可以对其进行编程以执行许多操作之一。默认情况下，它仍会在静音和响铃模式之间切换。但通过进入设置，您可以对其进行自定义以开始录音、打开相机、切换对焦模式等。在每个快捷方式中，您可以更准确地了解操作按钮的功能。假设您选择“相机”快捷方式。您可以点击下拉列表来选择是以常规照片模式还是以自拍、视频或肖像模式启动。</p><p>关于“操作”按钮值得注意的一件事是，除了默认模式之外，您还必须长按它才能真正启动快捷方式。如果您只是按下它，您会在按钮旁边看到一个屏幕指示器，告诉您按住它，而动态岛会发生变化以指示将启动的内容。我认为必须长按按钮才能真正触发我想要的东西会很烦人，但在花更多时间使用它时，我觉得启动动作可能太容易了。虽然我认为长按不一定能防止意外推动，但至少比简单的点击发生的可能性要小。这显然是我必须在现实世界中测试的东西，将其扔进我的钱包或腰包中，看看它会有多烦人。</p><p>我能够通过从远处拍摄媒体人物的照片来快速查看 iPhone 15 Pro Max 上的新变焦镜头。我使用 iPhone 14 Pro 从巨大的演示区域拍摄了迈克尔·费舍尔（又名 The Mr Mobile）的照片，将相机变焦至最大 15 倍。然后，我使用演示版 iPhone 15 Pro Max，使用最大 25 倍变焦，从稍远的地方拍摄了另一个人的照片。新手机的图像不仅更近，而且看起来更明亮、更清晰。</p><p>当然，在与更公平的设置进行现实世界的并排比较之前，我无法正确评估这一点，但我已经可以告诉你，在 iPhone 15 Pro Max 上，你会在左上角看到一个小窗口显示您在帧中放大的位置。这基本上也是所有具有极限变焦功能的手机（例如 Pixel 和 Galaxy 旗舰）的做法。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/fcabfdf0-51b3-11ee-bfbe-c7eb24fffb29" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/fcabfdf0-51b3-11ee-bfbe-c7eb24fffb29" style="height:960px;width:1280px;" alt="iPhone 15 Pro 悬在半空中。" data-uuid="9a7ff998-fcdb-3675-8e0b-98553d714b5e"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p> Most of the other changes to the iPhone 15 Pro line weren&#39;t things I could test at the demo area, like the performance of the new A17 Pro processor, the second-generation ultra wideband (UWB) chip and battery life. I did get a sense for how smooth the hardware-accelerated ray tracing looked as an Apple staff member played a bit of <em>Diablo IV</em> for me to see. I also couldn&#39;t plug a USB-C cable into the new port, of course, but I did spend a few minutes gawking at it while taking pictures.</p><p> I do like the way the new titanium material feels, though. The iPhone 15 Pros feature a brushed metal finish, and the Pro Max that I spent time with definitely felt noticeably lighter than its chonkster of a predecessor. The iPhone 14 Pro Max always felt like it would crush my skull if I dropped it on my face while reading in bed, while the new model felt like it would only gently dent my cranium.</p><p> I also briefly fondled a case made from Apple&#39;s new FineWoven material, which is meant to replace leather as the company ceases to sell items made from that. The case felt slightly furry, sort of like suede, and though no one said if this would change, it&#39;s the sort of texture I could see Apple tweaking over time. The idea is that suede also feels somewhat premium like leather, and though I prefer the feeling of leather over FineWoven, I can live with it if it means better things for the environment. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/af47bdc0-51bc-11ee-bbd2-a930f6911fca" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/af47bdc0-51bc-11ee-bbd2-a930f6911fca" style="height:960px;width:1280px;" alt="A pink iPhone 15 held in mid-air with its screen facing the camera." data-uuid="7f9869d5-161c-3518-93a5-011ed95e2dbf"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><h2> iPhone 15 and iPhone 15 Plus first impressions</h2><p> Of course, the Pros weren&#39;t the only new phones unveiled today. The iPhone 15s may be slightly less interesting, but they did get some potentially useful updates, too. They now feature 48-megapixel main cameras on their rear, supporting 24-MP default resolution pictures, and ditch the longstanding notch for the pill-shaped Dynamic Island cutout that was introduced last year.</p><p> I&#39;m a fan of the new colors on the iPhone 15 series, as well as the way they&#39;ve been infused into the back glass. It gives off a slight frosted effect that makes the pastel pink, blue, green, yellow and black hues look classy as opposed to cute. The phone&#39;s enclosure is also slightly different than the iPhone 14, with a contoured edge that makes the device feel slightly thinner.</p><p> I was taken by how much thinner the bezels on the iPhone 15s looked, too. Together with the contoured edges, brighter screens and losing the notch, the handsets feel refreshed and definitely like a bigger change than last year&#39;s models were.</p><p> There wasn&#39;t a lot more about the iPhone 15 line that I could check out at the demo area, but for all the details on what&#39;s new this year, check out our <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apples-iphone-15-has-a-48-megapixel-camera-and-the-dynamic-island-174520662.html">article laying out all the updates</a> .</p><p> <em>Follow all of the news live from Apple&#39;s &#39;Wonderlust&#39; event</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-event-2023-live-updates-on-the-new-iphone-15-160001658.html"><em>right here</em></a> <em>.</em></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-max-first-impressions-lights-camera-action-button-200647981.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/iphone-15-pro-max-first-impressions-lights-camera-action-button-200647981.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c91652e4-453a-457f-91fe-bdd5afcda470</guid><dc:creator> Cherlynn Low</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 12 Sep 2023 20:06:47 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694559522</ingested><modified> 2023-09-12T22:58:50+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|e